Notebook[{
Cell["Continuous functions on a closed interval", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"f37c6b01-4baf-48ba-b7c0-9fef99a429d7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Continuous functions are NOT part of this library's real-number theory \
\[Dash] ",
 "in the Lean blueprint they are the next chapter. But the point-set topology \
we ",
 "already have (open / closed / compact / connected) makes the classical \
theorems ",
 "on a closed interval fall out cheaply. Everything below is kernel-checked, \
0-sorry, ",
 "and lives in the demo file ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"demos", "/", 
   RowBox[{"Continuous", ".", "wl"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "82ce16b2-367f-4f5b-b8c4-3c68bbf606f2"],
 ". Evaluate the ",
 "cells top to bottom (Shift+Enter)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6fadadc8-1e47-41d0-80b3-a42542993fc0"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cf0f622d-1808-4a75-aff0-37db2e8d76b0"],

Cell["\<\
Load the kernel + stdlib snapshot and the continuity development:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c89c46a8-8fee-4ed7-bb73-32d2eda8d7bd"],

Cell["\<\
(* Load the kernel + stdlib snapshot, then the (demo) continuity theory. *)
root = ParentDirectory[NotebookDirectory[]];
Global`$HOLEncapsulationMode = \"Stable\";
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"bootstrap.mx\"}]];
$ContextPath = Join[
  Select[Contexts[], StringMatchQ[#, \"HOL`*\"] && ! StringContainsQ[#, \
\"Private`\"] &],
  $ContextPath];
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"demos\", \"Continuous.wl\"}]];
$ContextPath = Prepend[$ContextPath, \"HOL`Demos`Continuous`\"];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d624007c-cd5e-425c-9d22-a2f2d775974d"],

Cell["1. Continuity, topologically", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"51bbfcf7-facb-46ac-9d0c-4716858689e8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We use the topological definition: f is continuous when the preimage of \
every ",
 "open set is open. No epsilons, no limits \[Dash] just ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "isOpen"],ExpressionUUID->"aa6edf8b-5d50-4a24-8e0f-a2ac41a46715"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "PREIMAGE"],ExpressionUUID->"da73be48-294f-4e54-bd05-5e26ea75a956"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"27ed7356-7c98-4e8a-a157-367ecc1a57be"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousDefThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0bd1f61a-b101-4de7-8640-eb787c9c4a9a"],

Cell["2. The two image theorems", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"572a2219-74a0-4963-8d70-061f338f2110"],

Cell["\<\
The continuous image of a compact set is compact (pull an open cover of the \
image back through f, take a finite subcover, push it forward):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cc52fa3f-e01b-4018-bfdc-40a57552cf74"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageCompactThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7369d0f3-7ec5-4ee9-a076-858f830e6c44"],

Cell["\<\
The continuous image of a connected set is connected (a separation of the \
image pulls back to a separation of the domain):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f0794284-02d7-4f08-b659-01a2c4d91cb3"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageConnectedThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"e8a49ed8-46ac-4a26-8120-3db8707a28be"],

Cell["3. A closed interval is compact", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"91587bd6-8029-4ae7-b7e1-acafba0557cf"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is closed (Topology) and bounded (lo=a, hi=b), hence compact:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cf0156d2-262d-4d81-a6f6-1a4167a473c9"],

Cell["formatThm[closedIntervalCompactThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"41180adc-4fd6-4539-b784-625e87f1226e"],

Cell["4. Boundedness on [a,b]", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bfab93e0-e10d-44ac-9932-54246bf7e5b5"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is compact, so its continuous image is compact, hence closed and \
bounded \[Dash] in particular bounded. A continuous function on a closed \
interval is bounded:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0f8e337b-030c-4949-8cf2-72aef0b4e861"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageBoundedThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b7de4eb9-619c-4081-8092-afda3bde6b96"],

Cell["5. The intermediate value theorem", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2965cd35-c595-42fa-872e-f1096cac3713"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is also connected, so its continuous image is connected, hence an \
interval. Since the image contains f(a) and f(b), it contains every value \
between them \[Dash] the function-form IVT, proved from pure topology with no \
continuous-function analysis:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7e006319-6630-4c26-b875-f105f4d82e63"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousIVTThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"3f085fc7-d71e-4d17-88da-709e3228c2ea"],

Cell["6. The extreme value theorem", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8ad24cc1-0548-4261-9b52-47b7d848c8a8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The image of [a,b] is also compact, hence closed and bounded, so its \
supremum ",
 "is attained: there is a point where f reaches its maximum. The proof builds \
a ",
 "sequence approaching the supremum (each term within ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"n", "+", "1"}], ")"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8242ed61-addf-4de7-a1d6-41f4929d8997"],
 " of it), uses that a closed set contains its sequential ",
 "limits, and reads the maximiser off the resulting image membership:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f62884c9-ed3e-47ff-b117-3ffcd528fc55"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousEVTThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"6a90d58b-4df4-45f8-b4e9-d2f91c87053a"],

Cell["A live check", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"991759b4-a341-42c0-8f25-4e57076f2919"],

Cell["\<\
Each statement above is a real theorem object; the kernel built it. For \
example, the EVT has no hypotheses beyond the ones shown, and is genuinely a \
theorem:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c19402de-1ba6-4039-889f-827e30208b8c"],

Cell["{isThm[continuousEVTThm], hyp[continuousEVTThm]}", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"01cc8a6c-49fc-4960-8e7b-f51abaf4e24d"],

Cell["Next steps", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bdd82b70-c5a5-4d24-9d94-7ea978ed2da7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"demos", "/", 
   RowBox[{"Continuous", ".", "wl"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "16f848fe-dad9-4940-abc5-4aeb70336482"],
 " for the proofs and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"docs", "/", 
   RowBox[{"USER_GUIDE", ".", "md"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c1d2764c-85ae-4161-b023-5e6d6777fb0b"],
 " for the API."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6882e11d-2017-493e-8034-970cee5856dc"]
},
